{{See|Slip}}

==English==

===Pronunciation===
*slĭp, /slɪp/, /<tt>slIp</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪp|Rhymes: -ɪp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# An act or instance of slipping.
# A women's undergarment worn under a skirt.
# A small piece of [[paper]].
# A [[berth]] for a boat or ship.
# A mistake ([[slip of the tongue]].)
# {{uncountable}} In [[ceramics]], a thin, slippery mix of [[clay]] and [[water]].
# {{cricket}} Any of several [[fielding]] [[position]]s to the [[off side]] of the [[wicket keeper]], designed to [[catch]] the ball after being [[deflected]] from the bat; a [[fielder]] in that position (See [[first slip]], [[second slip]], [[third slip]], [[fourth slip]] and [[fifth slip]].)

====Translations====
*Dutch: slip {{m}} (1), slip {{f}} (2), [[ondergoed]] {{n}} (3), [[stukje]] [[papier]] {{n}} (3), [[kooi]] {{f}} (4)
*German:  [[Unterkleid]] {{n}} (2), [[Stück]] [[Papier]] (3)
*Spanish: [[braga]] (2)
*[[Telugu]]: [[చీటీ]] (cheeTee) (3)

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|slip||p}}

# {{intransitive}} To lose one's traction on a slippery surface.
# {{intransitive}} To [[err]].
# {{transitive}} To [[pass]] (a note, etc.)
#: ''The spy '''slipped''' his agent a coded message.''

